<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Legacy Heirloom | Monty's Archive</title>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:wght@500;700&family=Source+Sans+3:wght@300;400;600&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="../styles.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="page-header">
      <div class="container">
        <a class="back-link" href="../index.html">Back to Monty's archive</a>
        <h1>Legacy Heirloom</h1>
        <p class="intro">
          Monty's birthright comes with crested stationery, a family motto in Latin, and a lifelong reminder that his
          name is both invitation and obligation.
        </p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main class="container">
      <section class="cards-grid expanded-grid" aria-label="Legacy Heirloom details">
        <article class="card">
          <div class="card-link">
            <h2>Family Crest Origins</h2>
            <p>
              The Montgomery crest was commissioned in 1898 and features a rampant stag guarding a ledger—symbolising
              courage in commerce. Monty keeps a miniature version on his cufflinks.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <div class="card-link">
            <h2>Inherited Expectations</h2>
            <p>
              At age twelve he received a leather-bound book titled <em>Duties of the Third</em>, detailing which clubs to
              join, who to greet first at regattas, and how to correct a butler without losing poise.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <div class="card-link">
            <h2>The Annual Portrait Sitting</h2>
            <p>
              Every October, Monty is repainted for the ancestral portrait gallery. The painter keeps notes on preferred
              angles and the precise hue labelled “Montgomery confidence.”
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="page-footer">
      <div class="container">
        <p>Expanded archive entry for Monty's legacy heirloom.</p>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
